<!DOCTYPE ui:UiBinder SYSTEM "http://dl.google.com/gwt/DTD/xhtml.ent">
<ui:UiBinder xmlns:ui="urn:ui:com.google.gwt.uibinder"
             xmlns:g="urn:import:com.google.gwt.user.client.ui">

    <ui:with field="resources" type="com.bsteele.bsteeleMusicApp.client.resources.AppResources"/>

    <g:HTMLPanel >
        <div  style="margin: 10px;">
        <p>
            <button type="button" ui:field="songEnter">Enter Song</button>
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            <button type="button" ui:field="songEntryClear">Clear</button>
        </p>

        <p>
            Title:<br/>
            <g:TextBox ui:field="titleEntry" styleName="{resources.style.entryLine}" />
        </p>

        <p>
            Artist:<br/>
            <g:TextBox ui:field="artistEntry" styleName="{resources.style.entryLine}" />
        </p>
        <p>
            Copyright:<br/>
            <g:TextBox ui:field="copyrightEntry" styleName="{resources.style.entryLine}" />
        </p>
            <p>
                Key:<br/>
                <select ui:field="keySelection" >
                    <option value="Gb">G♭ 6♭</option>
                    <option value="Db">D♭ 5♭</option>
                    <option value="Ab">A♭ 4♭</option>
                    <option value="Eb">E♭ 3♭</option>
                    <option value="Bb">B♭ 2♭</option>
                    <option value="F">F 1♭</option>
                    <option value="C" selected="selected">C</option>
                    <option value="G">G 1♯</option>
                    <option value="D">D 2♯</option>
                    <option value="A">A 3♯</option>
                    <option value="E">E 4♯</option>
                    <option value="B">B 5♯</option>
                    <option value="Fs">F♯ 6♯</option>
                </select>
            </p>
        <p>
            Beats per minute:<br/>
            <g:TextBox ui:field="bpmEntry" styleName="{resources.style.smallIntEntry}" />
        </p>
        <p>
            Time Signature: 
            <select ui:field="timeSignatureEntry" >
                <option value="2/4" >2/4</option>
                <option value="3/4" >3/4</option>
                <option value="4/4" selected="selected">4/4</option>
                <option value="6/8" >6/8</option>
            </select>
        </p>
        <p>
            For chords and lyrics, mark the sections with the following:
        </p>

        <table>
            <tr>
                <td>
                    Chords:<br/>
                    <textarea rows="20" cols="30" ui:field="chordsEntry" style="font-size: large;" ></textarea>
                </td>
                <td>
                    <table>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Id</th>
                            <th>Alt</th>
                            <th>Section</th>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>V:</td>
                            <td></td>
                            <td>Verse</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>P:</td>
                            <td>Pc:</td>
                            <td>Pre-chorus</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>C:</td>
                            <td>Ch:</td>
                            <td>Chorus</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>B:</td>
                            <td>Br:</td>
                            <td>Bridge</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>I:</td>
                            <td>In:</td>
                            <td>Intro.  Is also used for interludes, riffs, theme, or hooks that don't quite fit other categories.</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>O:</td>
                            <td>Out:</td>
                            <td>Outro</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>Co:</td>
                            <td>Coda:</td>
                            <td>Coda</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td>T:</td>
                            <td>Tag:</td>
                            <td>Tag</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Chords must be in upper case for transcription to work!  (the transcription parser is turned off inside parenthesis but will continue afterwards).
                            For example:  A (pause) E D F</li>
                        <li>Using a lower case b for a flat will work.  A sharp sign (#) works as a sharp.</li>
                        <li>Limited set of case sensitive chord modifiers:  # b (m | maj | sus) [0-9]</li>
                        <li>Spaces between chords indicate a new measure.  Chords without spaces are within on measure.</li>
                        <li>Minus signs (-) can be used to indicate a repeated measure.</li>
                        <li>Periods (.) can be used to repeated chords on another beat witin the same meausure.  For example,
                            G..A would be three beats of G followed by a beat or A in the same measure.</li>
                        <li>Vertical bars (|) on the last measure  can be used to group repeats across multiple lines.</li>
                        <li>Forward slashes (/) can be used to indicate bass notes that differ from the chord.</li>
                        <li>Sample measures to use:
                            A B C G
                            A# C# Bb Db
                            C7 D7 Dbm Dm Em Dm7 F#m7 A#maj7 Gsus9
                            DC D#Bb G#m7Gm7 Am/G G..A
                        </li>
                        <li>Anything else not recognized is considered a comment to the end of the line.</li>
                        <li>As a comment use chorus or (Chorus) instead of Chorus,
                            otherwise it will be considered a C chord followed by the comment "horus".  
                            Bridge and Coda have the same problem.</li>
                    </ul>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <p>
            Lyrics:<br/>
            <textarea rows="60" cols="80" ui:field="lyricsEntry" style="font-size: medium;" ></textarea>
        </p>
        </div>
    </g:HTMLPanel>

</ui:UiBinder>